                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890b.6363 Gulf Oil Corporation/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-30T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 30, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 30—7:54
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. I delivered note (Department’s telegram 100, March 26, 4 p.m.) to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John Simon</persName> this morning who asked me to
                    assure you the matter was receiving his attention and memoranda for a draft
                    reply had already been compiled. The British position will be discussed at the
                    next Cabinet meeting which takes place on April 6th and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John</persName> stated he hoped immediately thereafter
                    to forward me a note of reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
